<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-17T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-17T10:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">362.1113 Velz, Roland/6:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany (<persName type="from">Dodd</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-17T16:00:00+01:00">October 17, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 17—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>171. My 168, October 15, noon. Neurath informed me this morning that
                                the two assailants of Velz came before a summary court yesterday and
                                were this morning sentenced to 6 months imprisonment each.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>